<hl>
<seg id=1> Thailand Financial Minister Tarrin Visit Japan on Financial Rescue Issue </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Agence Francaise de Press, Bangkok) - Thailand Financial Minister Tarrin left for Tokyo yesterday for negotiation on the Thailand part of a financial rescue package. The total amount of this package is at 30 billion US dollars (48.6 billion Singapore dollars) offered by Japan to rescue Asian member economies in financial crises. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> He said, he would have a through discussion during his four-day visit in Japan, but he could not expect how much Japan would give to Thailand. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Tarrin told the reporters at Bangkok airport:" I made a outline report of that loan to Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai, but we have not confirm the figure yet as Japan has not noticed us." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> He said, he hoped to have a low interest rate and generous repayment conditions from this plan. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> He said, he would have separate talks to officials of Japanese Minister of Trade and Industry on new aid to assist Thailand industry and reformation of agriculture. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Japanese Financial Minister Kiichi Miyazawa declared a financial rescue package of 30 billion US dollars in a group-seven conference on October 3th. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Within a short period, Japan will appropriate 15 billion US dollars to assist trade, and financing etc. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> Japan will offer direct financial aid in the ways of loans of Import and Export Bank of Japan and Asia bond purchasing, and offer Japanese yuan loans for development aid of Asian countries </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> She will also give guarantee for the bank loans of Asian countries and issuance of Asian bond, and to help them in international fund rasing. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=11> Kiichi Miyazawa's financial rescue package is critically important to Thailand because the latter just postponed her plan of issuance of 500 million US dollars of global bond. </seg>
<seg id=12> Thailand wants to utilize this money to inject more circulating capital to the economy. </seg>
<seg id=13> Thailand's economy is seriously attacked by high cost of debt and global new market storm. </seg>
</p>
